---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "@components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
import { SITE } from "@config/site";

const title = "Methodology: How We Research & What We Won't Claim";
const description =
  "How Home Sauna Guide researches buyer guides: the sources we use, the standards we hold, and the claims we deliberately avoid - no fabricated testing, ratings, or medical promises.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} type="article">
  <section class="editorial-container py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Methodology" }]} />
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-3xl">
      <h1>How we research, and what we won't claim</h1>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} publishes people-first buyer guides for home saunas. We would rather tell you what
        we do not know than fake authority. This page explains how our guides are built and the limits
        we hold ourselves to.
      </p>

      <h2>Where our information comes from</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturer specifications</strong> for dimensions, heater output, power draw, materials, and electrical requirements.</li>
        <li><strong>Independent expert reviews and sauna communities</strong> for real-world performance, durability, and the failure patterns owners report.</li>
        <li><strong>Electrical and building-code references</strong> for circuit, breaker, wire-gauge, chimney, and clearance guidance.</li>
        <li><strong>Peer-reviewed studies and major clinics</strong> (for example JAMA, Mayo Clinic, Harvard Health, Cleveland Clinic) for any health information.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we will not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>We do not fabricate testing.</strong> If we have not personally used a product, we say so and recommend by format and use-case instead of inventing a hands-on verdict.</li>
        <li><strong>We do not invent ratings.</strong> No made-up star scores or "best overall" trophies on gear we have not tested. We use Article, breadcrumb, FAQ, and list structured data only - never Review, Product, or AggregateRating markup without first-hand testing.</li>
        <li><strong>We do not overclaim health.</strong> We present sauna research conservatively, distinguish association from causation, cite primary sources, and never promise detox, weight loss, or disease cures.</li>
        <li><strong>We do not hide money.</strong> Affiliate links are disclosed on every page and never change our recommendations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Costs and estimates</h2>
      <p>
        Pricing on this site, including the sauna cost calculator, is presented as planning ranges
        synthesized from multiple 2026 industry sources and cross-checked against real build scenarios.
        Ranges are not quotes. For anything involving wiring, we tell you to get a written quote from a
        licensed electrician before buying.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates</h2>
      <p>
        Guides show a visible last-updated and last-reviewed date. As we add first-hand testing, we will
        publish those results separately and link them from the relevant guide rather than quietly
        rewriting history.
      </p>

      <p>
        Questions about how we work? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
